{"title":"SindromeFebrilAM","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Geriatría/SindromeFebrilAM iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Síndrome Febril\\Nen Persona Mayor","guid":"LfrUASMfFhJ416bS54mHHQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"DEFINICIÓN Y\\NPARTICULARIDADES","guid":"Sl0QJJ5Uk3n-RD2nncarsw","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Temperatura basal MÁS BAJA en AM → 36.4-36.7°C","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"CRITERIOS IDSA\\Npara fiebre en AM\\N(High 2009)","guid":"G_XybaQC7BQbS5gYd3QtqA","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"T° oral única >37.8°C (100°F)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"T° oral repetida >37.2°C (99°F)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"3","text":"T° rectal repetida >37.5°C (99.5°F)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"3","text":"Incremento >1.1°C sobre basal → CLAVE en frágil","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"AUSENCIA de fiebre\\NNO descarta infección","guid":"Ec307cZldM49guMvJN3L9A","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":">50% de AM con infección grave son AFEBRILES","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"Respuesta febril atenuada → inmunosenescencia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"Fiebre >38.3°C = definición general IDSA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"Fiebre >39.3°C = alta probabilidad infecciosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"1","text":"T° >41°C = sospechar hipertermia/causa neurológica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"14","parent":"0","text":"FISIOPATOLOGÍA →\\NINMUNOSENESCENCIA","guid":"wWJxs0AGtRCG8iKMurNQtw","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"Inmunidad\\Ninnata","guid":"vibhzxsQynpYhdZfxVJ0-A","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"Fagocitosis neutrofílica DISMINUIDA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"Producción de citoquinas alterada (IL-6 basal elevada)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"15","text":"Células NK → citotoxicidad reducida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"15","text":"Presentación antigénica deficiente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"14","text":"Inmunidad\\Nadaptativa","guid":"3mg5eD_ArsBmyly45UAdog","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Involución tímica → linfocitos T naive REDUCIDOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"Expansión clonal oligoclonal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"Respuesta humoral atenuada → vacunas menos efectivas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"Inmunosenescencia + inflammaging = paradoja","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"14","text":"Termorregulación\\Nalterada","guid":"5dqVZInJyW9fvhg887uV0w","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"Set point hipotalámico MODIFICADO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"Menor producción de pirógenos endógenos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"Vasoconstricción periférica reducida → menor escalofríos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"14","text":"INFLAMMAGING","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"Estado proinflamatorio crónico de bajo grado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"IL-6, TNF-alfa, PCR basalmente ELEVADOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"Dificulta interpretación de biomarcadores","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"PRESENTACIÓN ATÍPICA\\N→ CONCEPTO CENTRAL","guid":"tvTF8Te1i0_fT5u8nCgczw","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"Prevalencia ~33% de presentaciones atípicas en SU (Atallah 2015)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"DECLINACIÓN FUNCIONAL\\Ncomo signo cardinal","guid":"Y-h9g_cZ3nCKmYQIiUPVPw","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"Infección presente en 77% de episodios de declinación funcional (Berman 1987)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"Nueva confusión, incontinencia, caídas, deterioro movilidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"33","text":"DELIRIUM como\\Nequivalente febril","guid":"NSpcF0PazHTpqrg61BWoSA","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Especialmente en pacientes con TNCM previo → FACTOR INDEPENDIENTE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"Puede ser ÚNICA manifestación de infección","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"EJEMPLO CASO: Paciente 92a, TNCM mayor, 2 semanas más somnoliento → ITU por E. coli","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"33","text":"Síntomas clásicos\\NAUSENTES o atenuados","guid":"ydaOiIuRrAHnfqr_L8bWJQ","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"ITU → anorexia/malestar/náuseas MÁS FRECUENTES que disuria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"Neumonía → 44% sin fiebre, pero 92.5% con síntomas respiratorios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"Bacteriemia → caídas, malestar, cambio funcional/mental","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"33","text":"Factores de riesgo para\\Npresentación atípica","guid":"WFbYDcQ3O5EjnAIRNoIlNw","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"ITU complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"Demencia → factor independiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"Polifarmacia (antipiréticos crónicos, corticoides, AINES)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"Fragilidad severa","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"0","text":"ETIOLOGÍAS MÁS\\NFRECUENTES","guid":"qW0MfMkLKX0BDLEdM-XJfA","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"INFECCIÓN URINARIA\\N→ FOCO MÁS COMÚN","guid":"SnMe8ntIguiQRVN6ZZyL-Q","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"Incidencia 0.1-2.4/1000 días-residente en ELEAM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"PRECAUCIÓN → bacteriuria\\Nasintomática es PREVALENTE","guid":"QP7R6CSWCLm_ujutZIkHfg","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"20-50% en mujeres AM, 15-40% en hombres AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"54","text":"NO tratar bacteriuria asintomática (IDSA)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"54","text":"Urocultivo positivo ≠ ITU si no hay clínica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"52","text":"Criterios para ITU\\Nsintomática en AM","guid":"KGrYuNzKXiUTxfejul_zgA","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"Disuria aguda O","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"Fiebre (>37.9°C) + síntoma urinario nuevo/empeoramiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"Cambio en características de orina + síntomas sistémicos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"52","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → E. coli R ciprofloxacino\\Ny R cotrimoxazol >100.000 UFC","guid":"wUq0uHCf5ICJK_BYeEP6zg","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"OC con bacterias abundantes, placas de pus, nitritos (+)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"Dolor hipogastrio → localiza foco","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"62","text":"Falla a nitrofurantoína 100mg c/8h x 7d → persistencia febril 38°C","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"Considerar → ¿ITU complicada? ¿prostatitis? (antecedente HPB/prostatitis recurrente)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"51","text":"NEUMONÍA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Segunda causa más frecuente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"NAC en AM → mortalidad 10-30%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Criterios clásicos presentes en ~60% (tos, fiebre, rales)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"RxTx puede ser NEGATIVA en deshidratados → repetir 24-48h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"CURB-65 → score pronóstico (confusión, urea, FR, PA, >65)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"51","text":"INFECCIÓN DE PIEL Y\\NTEJIDOS BLANDOS","guid":"iuB3gysvWnfnWjj5JCfs6Q","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Celulitis en EV crónica/EVP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"Úlceras por presión infectadas → encamado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"73","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → encamado, sin LPP reportada → evaluar sacro/talones","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"77","parent":"51","text":"BACTERIEMIA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"15-22% sin foco identificable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"Mortalidad 18-50% en ELEAM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"77","text":"50% de muertes en <24h del diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"77","text":"Predictores → escalofríos, shock, bandas ≥1500, linfocitos <1000","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"77","text":"En AM → MENOS fiebre/taquicardia, MÁS falla renal/respiratoria","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"51","text":"INFECCIÓN\\NINTRAABDOMINAL","guid":"HT5vfIj_e8tdJ3ovU5NUXw","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Colecistitis → puede ser ALITIÁSICA en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"Diverticulitis → dolor localización variable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"Isquemia mesentérica → alto índice sospecha en FA","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"51","text":"OTRAS CAUSAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"Endocarditis → valvulopatía previa, dispositivos (marcapasos, stent)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"Meningitis → puede presentarse sin rigidez nucal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"87","text":"Artritis séptica → monoarticular, considerar prótesis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"87","text":"COVID-19, Influenza → estacionalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"87","text":"Tuberculosis reactivada → fiebre prolongada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"87","text":"C. difficile → uso recurrente de antibióticos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"94","parent":"0","text":"CAUSAS NO\\NINFECCIOSAS\\NDE FIEBRE","guid":"q8Y9Dbkv9etHtrAJ6gDj_w","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"Fiebre medicamentosa → antibióticos, anticonvulsivantes, alopurinol","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"94","text":"TVP/TEP → inmovilismo, encamado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"94","text":"Neoplasia → linfoma, carcinoma renal, hepatocarcinoma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"94","text":"Enfermedades autoinmunes → arteritis células gigantes, PMR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"94","text":"Fiebre post-ACV/hemorragia cerebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"94","text":"Gota/pseudogota → artropatía microcristalina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"94","text":"Reacción transfusional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"94","text":"Abstinencia OH/BZD","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"0","text":"ENFRENTAMIENTO\\NDIAGNÓSTICO EN\\NURGENCIAS","guid":"YoGkX7S2EuYftap0oW8zGw","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"PASO 1 → EVALUACIÓN\\NINICIAL RÁPIDA","guid":"erysPl01S7nS2rUF6sXW-A","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"ABCDE + signos vitales completos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"qSOFA → FR ≥22, PAS ≤100, GCS <15\\N(≥2 = sospecha sepsis)","guid":"SieAEq_M5jB5DL-f4McWYw","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"LIMITACIÓN en AM → GCS basal puede ser <15 (TNCM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"Mejor usar cambio respecto a basal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"104","text":"NEWS/NEWS2 → más sensible que qSOFA en urgencias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"104","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → somnoliento (cambio respecto a basal), T° 38°C, dolor hipogastrio","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"103","text":"PASO 2 → HISTORIA\\NCLÍNICA DIRIGIDA","guid":"hY3SB9w5WC67OyI-GMshFQ","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"ANAMNESIS\\NGERIÁTRICA\\Ndiferenciada","guid":"nzuIMe95RCUcZ45PP7WpGA","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"Funcionalidad BASAL (Barthel/Lawton previos) vs ACTUAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"Estado cognitivo PREVIO → para evaluar delirium","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"112","text":"Fármacos → antipiréticos, inmunosupresores, antibióticos recientes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"112","text":"Hospitalizaciones recientes → riesgo MDR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"112","text":"Dispositivos → sonda vesical, CVC, marcapasos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"112","text":"Residencia → ELEAM, domicilio, institución","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"111","text":"EJEMPLO\\NCASO","guid":"BTM0GY33hpjv71Wv2HeIYg","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"Barthel 5/100 (dependencia total) → deterioro progresivo 2 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"TNCM previo → cambio en nivel de conciencia = buscar causa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"Sept 2025 → bronquitis por Influenza A","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"119","text":"Nov 2025 → sepsis urinaria por Proteus mirabilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"119","text":"ATB recientes → nitrofurantoína, previamente tratado por Proteus","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"119","text":"Sin sonda vesical, sin CVC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"119","text":"Domicilio con 4 hijos → red de apoyo presente","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"127","parent":"103","text":"PASO 3 → EXAMEN\\NFÍSICO DIRIGIDO","guid":"trJJvaufaz9OwW9EK5Q68w","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"Piel → celulitis, LPP, eritema articular, exantema","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"Cardíaco → soplos nuevos (endocarditis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"127","text":"Pulmonar → crepitantes, matidez (consolidación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"127","text":"Abdominal → dolor localizado, peritonismo, globo vesical","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"127","text":"Extremidades → TVP, artritis séptica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"127","text":"Neurológico → rigidez nucal, signos focales nuevos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"127","text":"Genitourinario → puñopercusión lumbar, tacto rectal si prostatitis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"127","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → dolor hipogastrio (foco urinario), somnoliento orientado parcial","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"103","text":"PASO 4 →\\NLABORATORIO\\NESCALONADO","guid":"6Xcm2QQ1vfHy4yjBj1-SqQ","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"NIVEL 1\\N(inmediato)","guid":"-g8LYU-HO-6T5vU7UKjt0w","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Hemograma completo con diferencial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"PCR y/o PCT\\N(procalcitonina)","guid":"mXdBoJDZLh1y8EGfdAFP8g","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"PCR >30 mg/L → alta probabilidad infección bacteriana en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"139","text":"PCT >0.5 ng/mL → fuerte predictor bacteriemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"PCT <0.25 → bajo riesgo infección bacteriana","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"137","text":"Función renal (creatinina, BUN, electrolitos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"137","text":"Lactato → ≥2 mmol/L = disfunción tisular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"137","text":"Orina completa + urocultivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"137","text":"Hemocultivos x2 (periféricos) ANTES de ATB","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"136","text":"NIVEL 2 (según\\Nsospecha clínica)","guid":"MEqL1S_V2SQm44e9N96zjg","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"Rx Tórax","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"Ecografía POCUS → pulmón, vía biliar, vía urinaria, TVP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"147","text":"Gases arteriales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"147","text":"Pruebas hepáticas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"147","text":"Estudio LCR si sospecha meningitis/encefalitis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"136","text":"NIVEL 3 (si estudio\\Ninicial negativo)","guid":"ZFIJkUzWeldeF5TxyPRp4A","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"TC tórax-abdomen-pelvis con contraste","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Ecocardiograma → vegetaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"Panel viral respiratorio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"Galactomanano, beta-D-glucano si inmunosuprimido","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"158","parent":"136","text":"EJEMPLO CASO →\\Nexámenes externos 20/03","guid":"jKE-OMUiN0sH6neVFvdAdQ","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"Na 132.9 → HIPONATREMIA leve (¿dilucional? ¿SIADH por infección?)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"158","text":"PCR 6.1 → elevada pero moderada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"158","text":"Hb 13 → sin anemia significativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"158","text":"Leu 8200 → sin leucocitosis (NO descarta infección en AM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"158","text":"OC inflamatoria con pus y nitritos (+)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"158","text":"UC → E. coli R cipro/R cotrimoxazol >100.000 UFC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"158","text":"Faltan → hemocultivos, lactato, PCT, función renal (creatinina no reportada)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"0","text":"MANEJO EN\\NURGENCIAS","guid":"WDkXQGrLcsVELmLAH8wazw","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"RESUCITACIÓN SI\\NSEPSIS/SHOCK SÉPTICO","guid":"J35ATWTq6DlffsqzxlQ64w","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Cristaloides 30 mL/kg en primeras 3h → PRECAUCIÓN en IC/fragilidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"En AM frágil → bolos 250-500 mL con reevaluación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"POCUS para guiar volumen (VCI, líneas B pulmonares)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"171","parent":"167","text":"Vasopresores si PAM <65 después de volumen → norepinefrina primera línea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"167","text":"Lactato seriado como guía de resucitación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"167","text":"Surviving Sepsis Campaign 2021 → Hour-1 Bundle","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"166","text":"ANTIBIOTERAPIA\\NEMPÍRICA","guid":"QH8n-FOaA7w_5DKDWAKP2Q","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"INICIAR dentro de 1 hora si sospecha sepsis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"3 horas aceptable si infección no complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"174","text":"CONSIDERAR en AM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"Función renal → ajuste dosis (Cockcroft-Gault o CKD-EPI)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"Interacciones farmacológicas (polifarmacia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"177","text":"Riesgo de C. difficile → minimizar espectro","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"177","text":"ANTIBIOGRAMAS locales → conocer resistencia institucional","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"182","parent":"174","text":"ITU NO COMPLICADA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"Nitrofurantoína 100mg c/12h x 5-7d → NO en ClCr <30, NO en prostatitis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"182","text":"Fosfomicina 3g dosis única → alternativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"182","text":"Amoxicilina/clavulánico según antibiograma","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"186","parent":"174","text":"ITU COMPLICADA/SEPSIS URINARIA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"Ceftriaxona 1-2g/día IV → primera línea empírica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"Piperacilina/tazobactam si riesgo MDR o sepsis severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"186","text":"Ertapenem si BLEE conocida o sospechada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"186","text":"Meropenem si shock séptico + riesgo BLEE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"191","parent":"174","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → consideraciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"192","parent":"191","text":"Falla a nitrofurantoína → ¿resistencia? ¿prostatitis? (nitrofurantoína NO penetra próstata)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"191","text":"HPB + prostatitis recurrente → alta sospecha prostatitis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"191","text":"Si prostatitis → fluoroquinolonas (R) → cotrimoxazol (R)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"191","text":"Opciones → ceftriaxona IV (si sensible), considerar cefalosporina 3°G","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"191","text":"Hospitalizar → falla ambulatoria + fragilidad severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"174","text":"NEUMONÍA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"Ampicilina/sulbactam + macrólido → NAC hospitalizada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"Ceftriaxona + macrólido → alternativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"Piperacilina/tazobactam si aspiración o nosocomial","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"174","text":"PIEL/TEJIDOS BLANDOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"Cloxacilina o cefazolina → celulitis no complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"Vancomicina si SAMR sospechado","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"204","parent":"166","text":"CONSIDERACIONES\\NGERIÁTRICAS DEL\\NMANEJO","guid":"FwU-tryOrRVRBkOE1df-jA","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"FRAGILIDAD como\\Npredictor de outcomes","guid":"4xpde5ndNLaBV0aEPHRPDg","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"CFS ≥7 → mortalidad intrahospitalaria SIGNIFICATIVAMENTE mayor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → CFS 8 (dependencia total) → considerar proporcionalidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"208","parent":"204","text":"Objetivos terapéuticos\\N→ DISCUTIR con familia","guid":"rQM_DEf5tkziuicRcYGM3Q","children":[{"id":"209","parent":"208","text":"¿Ingreso UCI? → evaluar CFS, voluntades anticipadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"208","text":"¿Limitación esfuerzo terapéutico?","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"208","text":"Proporcionalidad → tratamiento activo vs confort","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"204","text":"Prevención de\\Ncascada iatrogénica","guid":"_xH8sLiIwAf0wOZtniYldw","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"Evitar sonda vesical innecesaria → MAYOR riesgo ITU","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"212","text":"Evitar restricción física → MAYOR delirium","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"212","text":"Movilización precoz si posible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"212","text":"Mantener ritmo sueño-vigilia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"212","text":"Desprescripción aguda de fármacos no esenciales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"204","text":"VGI ABREVIADA\\Nen urgencias","guid":"wyO2WTDlLF9T4CGW17f1Xg","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"CAM/4AT → delirium","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"CFS → fragilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"218","text":"Barthel previo vs actual → declinación funcional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"218","text":"Red social → destino al alta","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"223","parent":"0","text":"BIOMARCADORES EN AM →\\NINTERPRETACIÓN CAUTELOSA","guid":"d0EaV4GsEFCWpXRQf16ygg","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"PCR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"Sensible pero INESPECÍFICA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"224","text":"Basal elevada en inflammaging → >10 mg/L frecuente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"224","text":"Útil para seguimiento (tendencia > valor absoluto)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"228","parent":"223","text":"PROCALCITONINA\\N(PCT)","guid":"nukPYtzRznPOAzsfWLX9vA","children":[{"id":"229","parent":"228","text":"Más específica para infección BACTERIANA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"228","text":"<0.25 ng/mL → bajo riesgo bacteriano","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"228","text":">0.5 ng/mL → alta probabilidad bacteriana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"228","text":"Utilidad en DESESCALAMIENTO antibiótico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"228","text":"LIMITACIÓN → elevada en IRC, ICC descompensada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"234","parent":"223","text":"LACTATO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"235","parent":"234","text":"≥2 mmol/L = hipoperfusión tisular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"236","parent":"234","text":"≥4 mmol/L = shock séptico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"234","text":"FALSOS POSITIVOS en AM → insuficiencia hepática, metformina, convulsiones","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"223","text":"LEUCOCITOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"239","parent":"238","text":"LEUCOCITOSIS puede estar AUSENTE en AM con infección severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"238","text":"Leucopenia = signo de MAL PRONÓSTICO","guid":"YgFLZ-9WMbeqfhm8Ku8jaQ","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"238","text":"NEUTROFILIA con desviación izquierda → más útil que leucocitos totales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"238","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → Leu 8200 (normal) con infección confirmada","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"243","parent":"0","text":"DISPOSICIÓN Y\\NSEGUIMIENTO","guid":"rwybG3viJom_EdXSdgm-4w","children":[{"id":"244","parent":"243","text":"CRITERIOS DE\\NHOSPITALIZACIÓN","guid":"K4ol8Ms6VfVynGHFcvnnFw","children":[{"id":"245","parent":"244","text":"Sepsis (qSOFA ≥2, SOFA elevado)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"244","text":"Falla antibioterapia ambulatoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"244","text":"Imposibilidad de manejo oral (vómitos, disfagia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"244","text":"Fragilidad severa sin red de apoyo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"244","text":"Comorbilidad descompensada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"244","text":"EJEMPLO CASO → falla ATB + fragilidad severa + febril → HOSPITALIZAR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"251","parent":"243","text":"CRITERIOS PARA MANEJO\\NAMBULATORIO","guid":"Z07TjZwXWWEEN7J6jUY6rQ","children":[{"id":"252","parent":"251","text":"Estabilidad hemodinámica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"251","text":"Tolerancia oral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"251","text":"Red de apoyo efectiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"251","text":"Sin criterios de sepsis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"251","text":"Seguimiento asegurado en 48-72h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"257","parent":"243","text":"AL ALTA →\\NPLAN DE\\NACCIÓN","guid":"Sch0yOAIkas83KuJYzL20Q","children":[{"id":"258","parent":"257","text":"Antibiótico dirigido según antibiograma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"257","text":"Control clínico y laboratorio 48-72h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"257","text":"Signos de alarma escritos para familia/cuidador","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"257","text":"Reconciliación farmacológica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"257","text":"Evaluar necesidad de profilaxis ITU si recurrente","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"263","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"264","parent":"263","text":"AUSENCIA DE FIEBRE NO DESCARTA INFECCIÓN → >50% de AM graves son afebriles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"263","text":"Delirium/declinación funcional PUEDEN SER la ÚNICA manifestación infecciosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"266","parent":"263","text":"NO tratar bacteriuria asintomática → prevalente en AM, NO reduce morbimortalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"267","parent":"263","text":"Nitrofurantoína NO penetra tejido prostático → ineficaz en prostatitis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"263","text":"Leucocitos normales NO descartan infección grave en AM → buscar desviación izquierda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"269","parent":"263","text":"PCT <0.25 es útil para DESCARTAR infección bacteriana, pero considerar limitaciones en IRC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"263","text":"En AM frágil con ITU recurrente → evaluar causa subyacente (HPB, residuo vesical, litiasis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"263","text":"Hiponatremia + infección → considerar SIADH asociado a proceso infeccioso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"272","parent":"263","text":"En falla a ATB ambulatorio + CFS ≥7 → umbral bajo para hospitalización","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"273","parent":"263","text":"Siempre discutir PROPORCIONALIDAD TERAPÉUTICA con familia en frágil severo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"274","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"275","parent":"274","text":"1. High KP et al. Clinical Practice Guideline for the Evaluation of Fever and Infection in Older Adult Residents of LTCF: 2008 Update. J Am Geriatr Soc. 2009;57(3):375-394.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"276","parent":"274","text":"2. Berman P et al. The atypical presentation of infection in old age. Age Ageing. 1987;16:201-207.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"277","parent":"274","text":"3. Yoshikawa TT. Approach to the diagnosis and treatment of the infected older adult. In: Hazzard's Principles of Geriatric Medicine. McGraw-Hill; 1994.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"278","parent":"274","text":"4. Liang SY. Sepsis and other infectious disease emergencies in the elderly. Emerg Med Clin North Am. 2016;34(3):501-522.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"279","parent":"274","text":"5. Evans L et al. Surviving Sepsis Campaign: International Guidelines for Management of Sepsis and Septic Shock 2021. Crit Care Med. 2021;49(11):e1063-e1143.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"280","parent":"274","text":"6. Atallah F et al. Atypical presentations of older adults at the emergency department and associated factors. Eur Rev Med Pharmacol Sci. 2015.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"281","parent":"274","text":"7. Caterino JM et al. Age, nursing home residence, and UTI in US emergency departments. Acad Emerg Med. 2012;19(10):1173-80.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"282","parent":"274","text":"8. Fontanarosa PB et al. Difficulty in predicting bacteremia in elderly emergency patients. Ann Emerg Med. 1992;21:842-848.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"283","parent":"274","text":"9. Chassagne P et al. Is presentation of bacteremia in the elderly the same as in younger patients? Am J Med. 1996;100:65-70.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"274","text":"10. O'Grady NP et al. SCCM/IDSA Guidelines for Evaluating New Fever in Adult Patients in the ICU. Crit Care Med. 2023.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":284,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Geriatría","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Geriatría","filename":"SindromeFebrilAM iPad","id":"map_1008","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"SindromeFebrilAM iPad"}